WEBVTT

00:10.241 --> 00:12.448
♪ ♪

00:12.517 --> 00:14.379
- Well, it looks like
that's the last of it.

00:14.448 --> 00:16.068
- Yeah.
- Hmm.

00:16.137 --> 00:20.448
Before I go, a little gift
for my new star.

00:20.517 --> 00:24.413
- Oh, Penelope.
Oh, wow, they're gorgeous.

00:24.482 --> 00:25.689
Thank you.

00:25.758 --> 00:28.103
- Luca and I
are so excited

00:28.172 --> 00:30.655
to add you to our collection.

00:30.724 --> 00:32.068
I've gotta run,
but don't forget

00:32.137 --> 00:33.724
about our holiday party
tomorrow night.

00:33.793 --> 00:35.620
I cannot wait
to show you off.

00:35.689 --> 00:37.379
- Okay, I'll be there.
Thank you.

00:37.448 --> 00:38.689
- Wonderful.
Bye, ladies.

00:38.758 --> 00:40.310
- Bye.
- Bye.

00:40.379 --> 00:43.965
Wow, I can't believe they
bought all of your art.

00:44.034 --> 00:45.931
It's a little lonely
here without it.

00:46.000 --> 00:47.482
- Ah, you'll get over it.

00:47.551 --> 00:49.931
I nearly blacked out
when I saw that check.

00:50.000 --> 00:53.448
I can't wait to buy people
expensive Christmas presents

00:53.517 --> 00:55.655
instead of making them
homemade junk.

00:55.724 --> 00:57.517
- Should I stop making
your gift now?

00:57.586 --> 00:59.724
- Oh, no, no, no.
I love that scarf.

00:59.793 --> 01:01.344
- It's a poncho.

01:01.413 --> 01:03.172
- I knew that.

01:03.241 --> 01:04.793
- Hi, honey, what time
should I pick you up

01:04.862 --> 01:06.172
from Penn Station?

01:06.241 --> 01:08.137
- Dad's picking me up
from the school,

01:08.206 --> 01:10.206
so I'll just ride with him to
Rose's parents' party tonight.

01:10.275 --> 01:11.896
- Oh, so your dad
is definitely coming?

01:11.965 --> 01:14.137
- It's the one present
I requested for Christmas.

01:15.551 --> 01:17.827
- One night together
as a family.

01:17.896 --> 01:20.517
- Well, couldn't I just
crochet you something instead?

01:20.586 --> 01:22.517
- Hmm.
See you tonight!

01:26.103 --> 01:28.000
- Oh, my God.

01:28.068 --> 01:29.551
What did Nicolle Wallace do
to piss you off?

01:29.620 --> 01:31.310
I thought you liked her.
- No, I do,

01:31.379 --> 01:33.137
but arguing with her
intelligently on Twitter

01:33.206 --> 01:35.137
about immigration will move
the needle with Dem voters

01:35.206 --> 01:38.724
more than a screaming match
with Ann Coulter.

01:45.862 --> 01:48.034
- Holy shit.

01:48.103 --> 01:50.241
- I just got a text
from my agent.

01:50.310 --> 01:52.862
"New York Magazine"
is going to do an excerpt

01:52.931 --> 01:54.482
from my first chapter.

01:54.551 --> 01:57.034
- Ah, congratulations!

01:57.103 --> 02:00.034
- Thanks.

02:00.103 --> 02:02.448
- And you wrote the hell
out of that chapter.

02:02.517 --> 02:03.965
- Yeah, not until
you pushed me.

02:06.034 --> 02:07.965
Zane contributed a lot too.

02:08.034 --> 02:09.413
- Don't be so self-effacing.

02:09.482 --> 02:11.413
- That sounds like
Washington-speak.

02:11.482 --> 02:13.000
- Oh, no, you see,

02:13.068 --> 02:14.931
in D.C., we don't leave
our fingerprint on anything,

02:15.000 --> 02:16.586
unless it's polling
in the '70s.

02:16.655 --> 02:18.103
- Oh.

02:18.172 --> 02:20.310
- But I do think that
we make a very good team.

02:20.379 --> 02:22.379
- Mm-hmm.

02:24.310 --> 02:26.310
I have a breakfast meeting.

02:26.379 --> 02:30.034
- So do I.
Should we jump in the shower?

02:30.103 --> 02:32.689
What?
It'll be faster.

02:32.758 --> 02:34.517
Come on!

02:37.551 --> 02:44.586
♪ ♪

02:48.379 --> 02:51.482
- And lastly, I just want
to thank all of you

02:51.551 --> 02:54.931
for your hard work.

02:55.000 --> 02:56.586
It's been a tumultuous year,

02:56.655 --> 02:58.793
but you have been
extraordinary,

02:58.862 --> 03:01.655
and we're ending the year
on a bit of very good news

03:01.724 --> 03:04.103
from Millennial.
Kelsey.

03:04.172 --> 03:06.241
- Two pieces of good news,
actually.

03:06.310 --> 03:08.965
Well, first "Marriage Vacation"
was number two

03:09.034 --> 03:11.275
on the "Times"
Holiday Reads list.

03:11.344 --> 03:13.862
And we just got news
this morning

03:13.931 --> 03:15.793
that "New York Magazine"
is going to excerpt

03:15.862 --> 03:19.310
Jake Devereux's memoir
before publication.

03:25.172 --> 03:28.034
- You've both done
a tremendous job on the book,

03:28.103 --> 03:29.793
and I'm looking forward
to reading it.

03:29.862 --> 03:31.827
- Yeah.
- So that is all.

03:31.896 --> 03:33.793
Happy holidays
and thank you.

03:33.862 --> 03:35.482
- Hey, guys,
the magazine reached out

03:35.551 --> 03:37.275
and invited all of us
to their holiday party,

03:37.344 --> 03:38.586
if you're available.

03:38.655 --> 03:40.034
- Great.
Wouldn't miss it.

03:40.103 --> 03:41.724
- Okay.

03:41.793 --> 03:43.793
- Have a car at 7:30 at
my house for the party,

03:43.862 --> 03:46.965
and until then please keep
that epilepsy trigger

03:47.034 --> 03:50.793
as far away from my eyeline
as possible.

03:50.862 --> 03:53.482
- Hey, I just got that email

03:53.551 --> 03:55.482
from Jake's agent
before the meeting.

03:55.551 --> 03:56.931
Sorry if I sprung that on you.

03:57.000 --> 03:58.344
- Not sprung, I knew.

03:58.413 --> 04:00.862
How?

04:00.931 --> 04:03.379
- Who do you think leaked the
chapter to "New York Magazine"?

04:03.448 --> 04:06.758
- Wow.
You're good.

04:06.827 --> 04:09.827
- We're good.

04:09.896 --> 04:11.758
So what time
should we head out?

04:11.827 --> 04:15.000
- Oh, um, I'm gonna
have to meet you there,

04:15.068 --> 04:18.068
because I'm--
I'm getting a blowout.

04:18.137 --> 04:19.758
I'll see you there.

04:19.827 --> 04:21.862
- I'll see you there then.

04:27.275 --> 04:29.689
- Hey, congrats
on the excerpt,

04:29.758 --> 04:31.310
but I'm gonna have
to miss the party tonight.

04:31.379 --> 04:32.413
Why?

04:32.482 --> 04:34.206
- Oh, it's family stuff.

04:34.275 --> 04:36.517
- No! Oh, I need you there
to run interference.

04:36.586 --> 04:38.620
Jake and Zane.

04:40.034 --> 04:43.379
I'm kind of like
seeing both of them.

04:43.448 --> 04:46.344
Why didn't you tell me?

04:46.413 --> 04:48.724
- You have been gaslighting
an entire company

04:48.793 --> 04:50.413
since I met you.

04:50.482 --> 04:52.586
Can I have one secret?

04:56.103 --> 04:58.620
Oh, God.

05:02.206 --> 05:05.620
- Sergei,
it's Diana Trout in 4A.

05:05.689 --> 05:07.172
I'm expecting someone soon.

05:07.241 --> 05:08.827
If you can just send them up.

05:08.896 --> 05:10.413
He did

05:20.310 --> 05:23.034
- Surprise.

05:23.103 --> 05:25.586
- It's so full.

05:25.655 --> 05:27.965
So many pine needles.

05:28.034 --> 05:30.655
It'll be Christmas
all over my carpet.

05:30.724 --> 05:34.137
- You're welcome.
Could you, uh, scoot?

05:39.103 --> 05:41.172
There we go.

05:41.241 --> 05:43.241
Why don't you finish getting
dressed and I'll set it up?

05:45.241 --> 05:47.689
Or haul it away
if you really hate it.

05:47.758 --> 05:50.586
- I don't hate it.

05:50.655 --> 05:53.137
- Work on that
while you're in there.

05:59.000 --> 06:02.379
♪ ♪

06:02.448 --> 06:04.206
- Congratulations.

06:04.275 --> 06:06.586
The last political book
"New York Magazine" excerpted

06:06.655 --> 06:09.137
was "Fire and Fury,"
so you're in good company.

06:09.206 --> 06:11.448
- Well, I don't know
if I'm on that level, but--

06:11.517 --> 06:14.793
- Don't be so self-effacing.

06:14.862 --> 06:20.344
- Well, I do know that I am
lucky to be in such good hands.

06:20.413 --> 06:23.448
- Mm-hmm.

06:23.517 --> 06:25.413
- I am going to get us
some champagne.

06:27.931 --> 06:33.758
- ♪ I got one chance,
ooh, ooh, ooh ♪

06:33.827 --> 06:35.827
- Thank you.

06:35.896 --> 06:38.206
Success looks good on us.

06:38.275 --> 06:39.793
- We haven't even
finished the book.

06:39.862 --> 06:41.310
- And yet,
look at all these people

06:41.379 --> 06:42.793
already talking about it.

06:44.517 --> 06:46.310
- What's crazy is that
we got in on the ground floor

06:46.379 --> 06:49.827
of a huge wave of political
nostalgia in publishing.

06:49.896 --> 06:53.413
Ah, it's gonna be a big year
for us, Peters.

06:56.206 --> 06:58.655
What

06:58.724 --> 07:00.551
- Nothing that
I didn't do last weekend.

07:00.620 --> 07:02.310
- Okay, but last weekend
we were not at a party

07:02.379 --> 07:05.103
with our author and our boss.

07:05.172 --> 07:08.034
- Mistletoe.

07:08.103 --> 07:10.206
That's poinsettia.

07:10.275 --> 07:13.000
- Eh, close enough.

07:15.172 --> 07:16.655
- Jake, it has been a pleasure,

07:16.724 --> 07:19.551
but I have another
holiday party tonight.

07:19.620 --> 07:21.586
I look forward
to reading the book.

07:21.655 --> 07:23.310
- You know what,
let me walk you out.

07:23.379 --> 07:26.068
There's something I wanted to
talk to you about in private.

07:26.137 --> 07:29.310
- Yeah, please.

07:29.379 --> 07:32.517
- We should get going
to the party.

07:32.586 --> 07:35.724
You can deal with that later.

07:37.965 --> 07:39.586
That looks lovely.
Ready?

07:39.655 --> 07:41.241
- Slow down.

07:42.965 --> 07:44.827
One more thing.

07:49.758 --> 07:52.275
♪ ♪

07:52.344 --> 07:54.862
Do you like it?

07:54.931 --> 08:02.000
♪ ♪

08:06.379 --> 08:07.931
- Ooh!

08:08.000 --> 08:11.103
- Damn it.

08:14.965 --> 08:16.379
- Thank you so much
for inviting us.

08:16.448 --> 08:18.965
Your home is beautiful.
- Oh, thank you.

08:19.034 --> 08:21.068
- Where'd you get
the sweaters from?

08:21.137 --> 08:23.724
- Bad Hanukkah sweaters are
kind of our Christmas thing.

08:23.793 --> 08:25.655
- Yeah, and then
on Christmas Day,

08:25.724 --> 08:27.931
Bob makes his reindeer latkes,

08:28.000 --> 08:30.448
and we all make fun
of a bad Christmas movie.

08:30.517 --> 08:32.103
- Oh, I love that.
I love that.

08:32.172 --> 08:34.965
- So when will we see
the Miller family tradition?

08:35.034 --> 08:36.896
We don't really
have a family thing.

08:36.965 --> 08:39.620
- Oh, we most certainly do.

08:39.689 --> 08:41.172
- Yeah, Caitlin told me once
when we were drunk.

08:41.241 --> 08:43.517
It sounds hilarious.
- Don't play dumb, Mom.

08:43.586 --> 08:46.344
- Yeah, don't play dumb, honey.

08:46.413 --> 08:48.965
- Yeah!

08:49.034 --> 08:51.000
- Hey, no, that was our thing
when Caitlin was seven.

08:51.068 --> 08:53.310
- Well, yeah, we've done it
every year since.

08:53.379 --> 08:55.931
- We did in the privacy
of our own home.

08:56.000 --> 08:58.034
- Come on, the Katzes are
doing their family thing.

08:58.103 --> 09:00.103
Caitlin promised that
we would do ours.

09:00.172 --> 09:01.379
- Uh, have to.

09:01.448 --> 09:03.103
- I am dying to know
what it is.

09:03.172 --> 09:05.137
- Well, we can't 'cause David
didn't bring an instrument.

09:06.206 --> 09:07.758
- Oh, wait, it's in the car.

09:07.827 --> 09:10.862
- Ah!

09:10.931 --> 09:12.655
- Why does Dad know
about this and not me?

09:12.724 --> 09:13.862
- Because I knew
you'd make that face

09:13.931 --> 09:15.448
and try to get out of it.

09:15.517 --> 09:16.689
- Yeah, a drunk promise
is still a promise.

09:16.758 --> 09:19.068
- Please, Mom.
Please.

09:19.137 --> 09:21.034
- I just really want to see it.
- Please, please for me.

09:21.103 --> 09:24.172
- Please, please!

09:24.241 --> 09:27.000
- Okay, fine.

09:27.068 --> 09:28.517
- I'm gonna need an apron

09:28.586 --> 09:30.827
and, like, a gallon
of eggnog heavily spiked.

09:30.896 --> 09:32.517
- Yes!

09:32.586 --> 09:35.551
- You're doing it!
- Hell yeah, it's Miller Time!

09:35.620 --> 09:37.275
- Ugh, you're so weird.

09:37.344 --> 09:42.379
♪ ♪

09:42.448 --> 09:45.034
- ♪ High on the hill
was a lonely goatherd ♪

09:45.103 --> 09:47.344
♪ Lay-dee, oh-de-lay-dee,
oh-de-lay-hee-hoo ♪

09:47.413 --> 09:50.379
♪ Loud was the voice
of the lonely goatherd ♪

09:50.448 --> 09:52.862
♪ Lay-dee, oh-de-lay-dee,
oda-loo ♪

09:52.931 --> 09:55.344
- ♪ Folks in the town
that was quite remote heard ♪

09:55.413 --> 09:57.862
♪ Lay-dee, oh-de-lay-dee,
oh-de-lay-hee-hoo ♪

09:57.931 --> 10:00.655
♪ Lusty and clear from
the goatherd's throat heard ♪

10:00.724 --> 10:03.034
♪ Lay-dee, oh-de-lay-dee,
oda-loo ♪

10:03.103 --> 10:05.689
both: ♪ Yo-ho, lay-dee,
oh-da-lay-dee ♪

10:05.758 --> 10:08.137
♪ Oh yo ho,
lay-de-oh-de-lay ♪

10:08.206 --> 10:11.448
♪ Yo-oh, lay-dee-oh-de-lay ♪

10:11.517 --> 10:13.793
- Charles!
- ♪ Hey ♪

10:13.862 --> 10:16.172
♪ One little girl in
a pale pink coat heard ♪

10:16.241 --> 10:19.103
♪ Lay-dee, oh-de-lay-dee,
oh-de-lay-hee-hoo ♪

10:19.172 --> 10:20.896
- That's the woman we've been
wanting to set you up with.

10:20.965 --> 10:24.241
- I have been wanting
to set you up with.

10:24.310 --> 10:26.206
both: ♪ Yo-ho, lay-dee,
oh-da-lee-oh ♪

10:26.275 --> 10:29.275
♪ Yo ho, lay-de-oh-de-lay ♪

10:29.344 --> 10:32.241
- Her daughter
is Rose's roommate.

10:32.310 --> 10:34.586
- Don't worry about him.

10:34.655 --> 10:36.068
That's the ex.
Out of the picture.

10:36.137 --> 10:38.241
- This is just their
holiday tradition.

10:38.310 --> 10:39.517
- Huh.

10:41.931 --> 10:44.137
- ♪ Yo-de-lay-hee ♪
- ♪ Yo-de-lay-hee ♪

10:47.103 --> 10:52.241
♪ ♪

10:52.310 --> 10:55.000
both: ♪ Yo-de-lay-dee,
yo-de-lay, hey ♪

11:05.310 --> 11:07.965
- They're really good.
- Oh, excuse me, fraulein.

11:08.034 --> 11:11.137
There is someone
who would like to meet you.

11:11.206 --> 11:14.103
- Charles Brooks,
this is Liza Miller.

11:16.034 --> 11:18.206
- Very nice to meet you, Liza.

11:18.275 --> 11:19.862
- You too.

11:19.931 --> 11:21.931
- That's quite an act
you've got there.

11:22.000 --> 11:24.000
- Charles owns
a publishing company.

11:24.068 --> 11:27.034
- And didn't you used to work
in publishing, Liza?

11:27.103 --> 11:29.827
- When I was younger.

11:29.896 --> 11:31.862
A different life.

11:31.931 --> 11:33.413
- Well, you two have so much
to talk about.

11:33.482 --> 11:35.896
- There you are.
I want you to meet somebody.

11:35.965 --> 11:37.586
Oh, sorry, hi.

11:37.655 --> 11:40.206
- Um, this is Charles Brooks.

11:40.275 --> 11:41.655
He's a friend of the Katzes.

11:41.724 --> 11:43.482
This is my daughter, Caitlin.

11:43.551 --> 11:46.517
- Hi, Caitlin.
- Hi.

11:46.586 --> 11:48.413
Mom, Becky, just got here.

11:48.482 --> 11:49.586
I want you to say hello.

11:49.655 --> 11:51.206
- Oh, Becky.
I love Becky.

11:51.275 --> 11:52.827
- Yeah.
You've never met her.

11:52.896 --> 11:54.896
- Well, if you've met one
Becky, you've met 'em all.

11:54.965 --> 11:56.448
Right?
Excuse us.

12:01.379 --> 12:03.517
We can set you up
if you're interested.

12:03.586 --> 12:07.275
- She is definitely
interesting.

12:15.793 --> 12:17.482
- Good morning.

12:17.551 --> 12:18.965
- Oh, good morning.

12:19.034 --> 12:21.068
Who died and made you
Karl Lagerfeld?

12:21.137 --> 12:23.275
- I'm just trying on looks
for Penelope's party.

12:23.344 --> 12:25.206
Do you think I could
pull off a harness?

12:25.275 --> 12:27.551
- Hmm, that's a choice every
woman has to make for herself.

12:29.172 --> 12:31.413
- Ugh, David kept putting
his arm around me,

12:31.482 --> 12:33.310
and Caitlin goaded me
into yodeling

12:33.379 --> 12:34.758
in a roomful of strangers.

12:34.827 --> 12:36.758
- Oh, just like
Norman Rockwell painted it.

12:36.827 --> 12:39.068
- And then Charles showed up.

12:39.137 --> 12:41.068
- In braids and
a makeshift dirndl

12:41.137 --> 12:43.103
while David played
the accordion.

12:43.172 --> 12:44.689
- Oh, this is the worst
secondhand embarrassment

12:44.758 --> 12:46.827
I've ever felt, and my cousin
is still in "Stomp."

12:46.896 --> 12:48.758
- Yeah, I can't wait to never
talk about it again.

12:48.827 --> 12:50.241
Hi, good morning.

12:50.310 --> 12:51.896
- Ugh, I thought you were
making breakfast.

12:53.551 --> 12:56.931
This is for infants.
- It's for hangovers.

12:57.000 --> 12:59.206
- Hey, Tilda Swinton.
- I'll take it.

12:59.275 --> 13:02.310
Ah, what's up, Caitlin?

13:02.379 --> 13:04.103
I, uh, I just wanted to
drop off some presents

13:04.172 --> 13:05.413
before I head
to my mom's tonight.

13:05.482 --> 13:06.827
- Oh.
- Oh, that's so sweet.

13:06.896 --> 13:08.862
Thank you.
- Don't get too excited.

13:08.931 --> 13:10.448
It's just a little
something I made.

13:10.517 --> 13:12.413
- So is mine.

13:13.931 --> 13:15.689
Sorry, I didn't have time
to wrap it.

13:15.758 --> 13:17.068
- Oh.
- Merry Christmas.

13:17.137 --> 13:18.931
- It's perfect.

13:19.000 --> 13:20.206
- Yay.
- I love it, thank you.

13:20.275 --> 13:22.137
- You're so welcome.

13:22.206 --> 13:25.689
- Merry Christmas.
- Merry Christmas. Thank you.

13:25.758 --> 13:27.551
- You and Josh are
hanging out again?

13:27.620 --> 13:29.862
- No, we're just friends.

13:29.931 --> 13:33.137
"It's perfect."
Ah, he still loves you!

13:33.206 --> 13:34.758
- And I am still
too old for him.

13:34.827 --> 13:36.482
- Since when does he care
that you're old?

13:36.551 --> 13:38.551
- Since I am your mom.

13:38.620 --> 13:41.275
And my romantic relationships
are none of your business.

13:44.344 --> 13:46.000
♪ ♪

13:48.034 --> 13:49.689
- I did, yeah.
Come on in, have a seat.

13:49.758 --> 13:52.482
- You left before the party
got going last night.

13:52.551 --> 13:55.655
Everybody was talking about
Devereux and Millennial.

13:55.724 --> 13:57.482
We're gonna have to hunker down
and work the rest

13:57.551 --> 13:59.620
of that book over pretty hard
over the break.

13:59.689 --> 14:01.586
- That is actually
what I wanted to discuss.

14:01.655 --> 14:03.482
Before I left last night,

14:03.551 --> 14:06.379
Jake said he feels the process
could use some--

14:06.448 --> 14:08.172
um, some streamlining.

14:08.241 --> 14:10.206
- Whatever he wants,
I'm sure we can accommodate.

14:10.275 --> 14:12.586
- He would prefer
to work with Kelsey

14:12.655 --> 14:15.344
for the rest of the book.

14:15.413 --> 14:18.137
Why?

14:18.206 --> 14:20.275
Zane and I both worked
on that chapter.

14:20.344 --> 14:22.482
He's the reason
it's in the magazine.

14:22.551 --> 14:24.793
- He said he doesn't want
to tie up two editors

14:24.862 --> 14:26.655
when one could do the job.

14:26.724 --> 14:28.517
Now, he was very--

14:28.586 --> 14:29.724
- Political.

14:29.793 --> 14:31.310
- Diplomatic.

14:34.000 --> 14:36.034
- Well, at the end of the day,

14:36.103 --> 14:38.655
the author gets
what the author wants.

14:38.724 --> 14:40.344
Right, Peters?

14:46.689 --> 14:49.689
- Zane.
Zane, slow down.

14:58.000 --> 15:00.344
- Do you wanna tell me what
that was or should I guess?

15:00.413 --> 15:01.931
- I didn't orchestrate that.

15:02.000 --> 15:03.310
- Okay, I'll guess.

15:03.379 --> 15:05.275
There's something going on
between you two.

15:05.344 --> 15:06.724
Right?

15:08.379 --> 15:09.931
- I knew he had
a thing for you.

15:10.000 --> 15:12.275
I should have stopped this
the second I saw it.

15:12.344 --> 15:14.931
- I did not ask Jake
to take you off the book.

15:15.000 --> 15:17.000
- Well, he did.

15:17.068 --> 15:20.586
And now you have your
bestseller all to yourself.

15:20.655 --> 15:22.793
I hope it was worth it.

15:25.862 --> 15:32.896
♪ ♪

15:41.275 --> 15:46.275
- It was very nice
to meet you last night.

15:46.344 --> 15:47.620
Very charming.

15:47.689 --> 15:49.310
Try humiliating.

15:49.379 --> 15:50.965
- No, not at all.

15:51.034 --> 15:52.448
- You saw me yodel.

15:52.517 --> 15:54.241
You might as well
have seen my naked.

15:54.310 --> 15:56.758
Not that I'm
recommending that either.

15:56.827 --> 15:59.551
I'm--I'm gonna go.
Merry Christmas.

15:59.620 --> 16:02.689
- Wait.

16:02.758 --> 16:05.620
So is this an annual thing?

16:05.689 --> 16:08.206
- It was when we were
still together.

16:08.275 --> 16:10.620
We did it once
when Caitlin was little,

16:10.689 --> 16:14.724
and she begged us
every year after that.

16:14.793 --> 16:17.310
I guess it meant more to her
than I realized.

16:19.793 --> 16:23.206
- A few years ago, we, uh--
we hosted an Easter egg roll,

16:23.275 --> 16:26.137
and the bunny cancelled,
so I had to step in.

16:26.206 --> 16:29.413
I was hunched over in that
costume for three hours.

16:29.482 --> 16:31.206
Soaked in sweat.

16:31.275 --> 16:33.517
It's amazing, the things
that we do for our kids.

16:33.586 --> 16:36.413
Isn't it?

16:36.482 --> 16:40.586
- Caitlin's why I work
so hard for my job.

16:40.655 --> 16:42.586
Why I did what I did.

16:42.655 --> 16:47.034
♪ ♪

16:47.103 --> 16:50.379
Anyway, um, what are
you doing for the holidays?

16:50.448 --> 16:53.655
Uh, Pauline has the girls
for a few days,

16:53.724 --> 16:55.551
so I'm going skiing,
and then I'm gonna meet them

16:55.620 --> 16:58.655
at their grandparents' house
in Florida.

16:58.724 --> 16:59.862
And you?

16:59.931 --> 17:01.551
- Caitlin's with me all week.

17:01.620 --> 17:04.137
So I'll probably just
be tracking her phone

17:04.206 --> 17:06.000
and panicking the entire time.

17:06.068 --> 17:07.827
- So is that what I have
to look forward to?

17:07.896 --> 17:09.586
- Oh, no, you have two of them.
It's going to be much worse.

17:11.655 --> 17:15.379
♪ ♪

17:15.448 --> 17:17.241
Um...I should, um,

17:17.310 --> 17:19.103
I should probably
get this to Diana.

17:19.172 --> 17:22.379
- Yes.

17:25.448 --> 17:32.241
♪ ♪

17:34.517 --> 17:36.275
Liza, I'm leaving
for the holidays,

17:36.344 --> 17:37.689
but I wanted to give you this.

17:37.758 --> 17:39.241
- Diana, that's so sweet.

17:39.310 --> 17:41.000
I thought you weren't
a Christmas person.

17:41.068 --> 17:42.793
- I'm not, but Enzo got a tree,

17:42.862 --> 17:45.551
and it looked empty
with no gifts under it, so...

17:45.620 --> 17:46.862
- I like this guy for you.

17:46.931 --> 17:48.241
- Enough about him.
Open it.

17:48.310 --> 17:51.137
- Oh.

17:51.206 --> 17:53.896
Ohh.

17:55.482 --> 17:57.379
It's gorgeous.

17:57.448 --> 18:00.413
- Neckwear should inspire envy,
Liza, not seizures.

18:00.482 --> 18:02.482
- Thank you.

18:02.551 --> 18:05.172
Diana, oh, uh, here.

18:05.241 --> 18:07.827
It's nothing extravagant,
but...

18:20.620 --> 18:23.862
Thank you, Liza.
Never give it up.

18:23.931 --> 18:26.206
The wealth disparity just makes
it awkward for both of us.

18:26.275 --> 18:27.275
- Of course.

18:27.344 --> 18:29.000
- Oh, uh, one more thing.

18:29.068 --> 18:31.724
From Charles, your bonus.

18:31.793 --> 18:34.310
More that I approved, but...

18:34.379 --> 18:37.517
you earned it.

18:37.586 --> 18:39.103
Merry Christmas.

18:39.172 --> 18:41.103
- Merry Christmas.

18:44.172 --> 18:51.172
♪ ♪

19:03.000 --> 19:05.034
Oh, hi, George.

19:05.103 --> 19:07.034
- You just missed him.

19:07.103 --> 19:09.793
♪ ♪

19:15.206 --> 19:17.034
- Let me know when
you'd like me to come by

19:17.103 --> 19:18.620
to help install my art.

19:18.689 --> 19:20.689
- Of course, I will definitely
keep you posted.

19:20.758 --> 19:22.034
- Great.

19:22.103 --> 19:24.586
- Maggie Amato,
this is Akilah Jeffries.

19:24.655 --> 19:27.827
- Akilah, oh,
I'm such a huge fan.

19:27.896 --> 19:29.517
I loved your
lighting installation

19:29.586 --> 19:31.620
in Battery Park
during Occupy.

19:31.689 --> 19:33.034
- Well, thank you, my dear.

19:33.103 --> 19:35.137
Are you coming to St. Bart's
in February?

19:36.689 --> 19:37.931
- She doesn't know it yet,
but she is.

19:38.000 --> 19:40.275
- It's a fabulous
artists' retreat.

19:40.344 --> 19:43.379
We get a house and a yacht
and we just unplug.

19:43.448 --> 19:46.310
- I'm always my freest
in St. Bart's.

19:46.379 --> 19:48.379
- Tell her how much fun
it is, Akilah.

19:51.482 --> 19:53.620
- So what are you
working on lately?

19:53.689 --> 19:56.137
I can't remember the last time
I saw one of your exhibits.

19:56.206 --> 19:57.862
- Oh, it's been a minute.

19:57.931 --> 19:59.758
I've slowed down somewhat
since Penelope and Luca

19:59.827 --> 20:01.448
bought my entire collection.

20:01.517 --> 20:03.965
- Oh, wow, me too. Where are
they displaying your pieces?

20:04.034 --> 20:06.965
- All in storage.
We're an investment now.

20:07.034 --> 20:08.827
Not that I'm complaining.

20:08.896 --> 20:11.586
I went to Turks and Caicos
twice last year.

20:11.655 --> 20:13.724
- Yo, I don't know that
there's an SPF high enough

20:13.793 --> 20:15.965
for me to handle
that many Caribbean retreats.

20:16.034 --> 20:19.034
- It's not really up to you
anymore, dear.

20:20.655 --> 20:22.827
- Did Penelope
give these to you?

20:22.896 --> 20:25.482
- Mm-hmm.

20:25.551 --> 20:27.827
- A little on-the-nose.
Don't tell her I said that.

20:27.896 --> 20:30.413
She thinks it's clever.

20:30.482 --> 20:32.172
- A toast to St. Bart's.

20:32.241 --> 20:34.103
- St. Bart's.
- I can't make it.

20:34.172 --> 20:36.310
I'm sorry.

20:36.379 --> 20:38.275
I'm really thankful
for everything,

20:38.344 --> 20:40.413
but I just don't feel
that I'm the right fit

20:40.482 --> 20:42.103
for your collection.

20:43.448 --> 20:45.103
- I didn't make
all of this work

20:45.172 --> 20:47.896
for it to be buried
in the artistic Sunken Place.

20:49.517 --> 20:52.103
Merry Christmas.
Good night.

20:56.965 --> 21:01.827
♪ ♪

21:01.896 --> 21:03.482
- Josh.
- Hey.

21:03.551 --> 21:05.517
- Hey!

21:05.586 --> 21:07.310
- Uh, nothing.

21:07.379 --> 21:09.793
I just, um, wanted to wish
you a merry Christmas.

21:09.862 --> 21:11.965
- Merry Christmas.

21:12.034 --> 21:15.517
Just heading to LaGuardia,
so...

21:15.586 --> 21:17.103
- Hey, I don't know
what happened

21:17.172 --> 21:19.586
between you and my mom,

21:19.655 --> 21:21.862
but I hope you guys
work it out.

21:21.931 --> 21:23.344
- What, did she say
something to you?

21:23.413 --> 21:25.482
- No, but...

21:25.551 --> 21:29.379
you're the best thing to happen
to her in a long time.

21:29.448 --> 21:32.206
You're good for her.

21:32.275 --> 21:34.344
- Whatever you say.

21:34.413 --> 21:36.448
- Just don't give up on her.

21:36.517 --> 21:38.862
Okay?

21:38.931 --> 21:40.310
- Okay.

21:40.379 --> 21:41.620
- Good.

21:41.689 --> 21:43.344
Have a good holiday.

21:43.413 --> 21:47.000
- Yeah, you too.
Yeah.

21:50.103 --> 21:52.896
- I told you the side streets
would be a mess in the snow.

21:52.965 --> 21:54.413
We should have taken the BQE.

21:54.482 --> 21:56.172
- It's fine.

21:58.000 --> 21:59.931
- ♪ High on a hill
was a lonely goatherd ♪

22:00.000 --> 22:01.896
♪ Lay-ee, oh-de-lay-dee,
oh-de-lay-hee-hoo ♪

22:01.965 --> 22:03.620
♪ That was the voice of... ♪

22:03.689 --> 22:07.206
- The beloved classic
returns to Broadway.

22:07.275 --> 22:09.793
- ♪ Folks in a town
that was quite remote heard ♪

22:09.862 --> 22:11.655
- Actually,
can you turn around?

22:11.724 --> 22:13.206
I'm not gonna go
to the airport.

22:13.275 --> 22:14.896
- First chance I get, boss.

22:14.965 --> 22:17.620
- ♪ Yo-del-ay, yo-del-loo ♪

22:24.793 --> 22:27.034
- ♪ I know I can't ♪

22:29.000 --> 22:32.758
♪ I can't be everything
I want ♪

22:32.827 --> 22:35.965
♪ All in one ♪

22:36.034 --> 22:37.896
♪ Just the one for you ♪

22:37.965 --> 22:41.689
♪ We make up,
up some pieces ♪

22:41.758 --> 22:44.931
♪ Puzzle pieces ♪

22:45.000 --> 22:48.379
- What are you--
- I don't care anymore.

22:48.448 --> 22:51.551
- ♪ We fit all adding up ♪

22:51.620 --> 22:53.896
♪ ♪

22:53.965 --> 22:56.517
♪ If you want
a second to breathe ♪

22:56.586 --> 22:58.172
♪ I'll give you
all of my love ♪

22:58.241 --> 23:00.551
♪ I'll give you
all that you need ♪

23:00.620 --> 23:03.137
♪ Don't worry,
I'm not in a hurry ♪

23:03.206 --> 23:06.827
♪ Not going nowhere,
I'm not going nowhere ♪
